description:
**WHAT DOES A MITIGATION TECHNICIAN WITH PAUL DAVIS DO?**  

* Serve others within your community in their time of need;
* Make a difference for others that have had a disaster strike their property;
* Work hard and take pride in completing projects (i.e. mitigating flood and fire damage);
* Be empathetic and show a sense of urgency while communicating through modern technology.



**WHY JOIN THE TEAM?** Paul Davis is an industry leader in restoration and reconstruction for insurance providers and both commercial and residential properties throughout the U.S. and and Canada. Paul Davis Restoration of Metro New York is headquartered in Queens and serves the broader New York City Metropolitan Area. We are growing locally and have career opportunities for individuals who want purpose out of their work. We view every Mitigation Technician as a long-term hire. We hire only dedicated “A Players”, with the goal of developing them to become experts in the field and future leaders in our company. We provide excellent professional training and a great company culture. Our employees are all treated with love, respective, and appreciation. The vast majority of our employees have been with us for over five years.  



Mitigation Technicians will be responsible for providing on-site services to our customers, and will work in teams alongside Senior Technicians, Supervisors, and Management. Mitigation Technicians will be in frontline contact with customers during projects and must represent the company in a positive manner that builds customers’ confidence and trust in our work. Primary tasks include: (1) evaluating and recording damages to a building caused by water, fire, mold, storm, etc.; (2) cleaning and restoring damaged structures, using our professional and specialized equipment and techniques; (3) directly communicating with customers and coordinating with the Paul Davis team to provide extraordinary customer care; and (4) embodying our office’s core values of honesty, integrity, and safety. Mitigation Technicians may also from time to time be asked to support other aspects of our office's operations and growth strategy.  



**OUR VALUES:** Deliver what you promise. Respect the individual. Have pride in what you do. Practice continuous improvement.  



**OUR VISION:** To provide extraordinary care while serving people in their time of need.  



**OUR MISSION:** To provide opportunities for great people to deliver Best in Class results.  



**WHY THE TEAM NEEDS YOU?** Serving others after a disaster has struck their property is not easy. Everyone within Paul Davis needs to have a world-class work ethic, serious attention to detail and love to help people. You will love being a Technician if you take pride in your work and have a genuine interest in learning and helping others.  



**Reports To: Mitigation Manager**  



**POSITION REQUIREMENTS:**  

* High character with uncompromising commitment to honesty and integrity;
* Hardworking attitude, and adaptability to work hours that sometimes can be long or irregular (including on weekends);
* Ability to operate in hazardous environments with care and safety;
* Strong attention to details;
* Genuine desire to help other people;
* Demonstrated record of responsibility, teamwork, and respect for people and properties;
* High school diploma or equivalent;
* Legal authorization to work in the U.S.



**PREFERRED SKILLS & EXPERIENCES:**  

* 2-4 years of post-high-school education/training, or an honorable discharge from the U.S. Armed Forces;
* Construction, renovation, or handyman experience and knowledge;
* Technical proficiency with smart phones and tablets, and ability to learn new software and tools;
* Strong communication skills (both oral and written);
* Desire to learn new things and growth within the company;
* Ability to manage other people and projects;
* If limited experience but you meet all Position Requirements, it's okay; we will invest in your training!



**COMPENSATION & BENEFITS:**  

* Highly competitive hourly wage (varies based on experience level and personal growth), with significant opportunity for overtime pay each week;
* All employees paid weekly!
* Eligible for full benefits after 90 days of employment, including health and disability insurance, earned vacation days and sick days, 401(k) with company matching, monthly cellphone allowance, and additional annual performance-based bonuses.
* Significant cross-training and career growth opportunities!



**NOTE:** If you have relevant previous experience and IICRC certifications, you may be eligible to start immediately as a Senior Mitigation Technician (and earn even higher pay).  



Please apply if you think you have what it takes to be a team-player and and deliver world-class service when others need it the most. We are looking forward to discussing this opportunity with you.  



**We love to support and hire Veterans and we are an Equal Opportunity Employer!**

***Supply Chain Buyer***





Whippany Actuation Systems is a dynamic aerospace company that designs and manufactures electromechanical actuators and control electronics for commercial and military applications. Recognized as experts in our industry for over 75 years, we are a fully integrated manufacturing company which takes responsibility for the success of our business and acts quickly to implement new ideas and projects to ensure company growth.





We are looking for a results-driven and growth-oriented individual to join our purchasing department as our newest Supply Chain Buyer. Your primary focus will be to manage supplier relationships and coordinate the procurement of materials, components, and services for the facility. In this demanding role, you will monitor, plan, and ensure the timely and cost-effective delivery of supplies and materials. You will also support new product development and implementation initiatives utilizing project management techniques and lead strategic projects supporting new business initiatives.





***In this role, you will typically:***


* Achieve the lowest possible cost for material, balanced against optimum quality and schedule needs;
* Solicit and evaluate proposals employing appropriate negotiation, cost and price analysis techniques to achieve the lowest possible cost for material, balanced against optimum quality and schedule needs;
* Evaluate current and anticipated requirements through the use of ERP/MRP action plans and reports;
* Implement purchase contracts with sound purchasing practices and assure compliant acquisition of material or service that meet applicable company and government regulations;
* Support new product introduction/development to assure Sourcing is providing the best possible solution;
* Work closely with Program Management, Operations, Engineering and Quality staff to ensure production schedules are met to achieve customer on-time deliveries;
* Manage all Purchase Order (PO) activities such as: PO creation, PO changes, Vendor Return Material Authorizations (VRMA), Return to Vendor (RTV), and Invoice issues;
* Support the Purchasing department and management with special projects and assignments.


***We require:***


* A Bachelor's degree in Supply Chain Management, Business Administration or a related field from an accredited university or college;
* 2 years' experience in a sourcing or planning role;
* Experience in a manufacturing environment;
* An ability to travel up to 10%;
* Authorization to work in the US


**Eligibility Requirements****:**



This role is restricted to U.S. persons (i.e., U.S. citizens, permanent residents, and other protected individuals under the Immigration and Naturalization Act, 8 U.S.C. 1324b(a)(3)) due to access to export-controlled technology. Whippany Actuation Systems will require proof of status before employment.





***We would really like to see:***


* APICS/ASCM Certification preferred;
* Strong interpersonal and leadership skills;
* Enterprise Resource Planning (ERP) systems experience;
* Knowledge of federal acquisition regulations;
* Demonstrated ability to manage changing priorities and ensure supplier commitments are met;
* Ability to build and develop supplier relationships and foster future new supplier sources;
* Experience sourcing mechanical components;
* Strong oral and written communication skills;
* Demonstrated ability to make decisions and implement appropriate actions with limited supervision;
* Proficiency with Microsoft Office and Project Management tools.


***What do we offer:***


* Competitive compensation
* Generous paid time off including 12 paid holidays
* 9/80 Schedule (every other Friday off)
* 401K with immediate company match up to 4%
* Medical, dental, vision benefits effective on 1st of the month after hire date
* Company provided Life and Disability Insurance
* Tuition assistance program


For more information and to apply, please visit our website @ www.whipactsys.com/careers





***Our Commitment:***





Whippany Actuation Systems is an Equal Opportunity / Affirmative Action Employer. We are committed to hiring and retaining a diverse workforce. Employment decisions are made without regard to race, color, religion, national or ethnic origin, sex, sexual orientation, gender identity or expression, age, disability, protected veteran status or other characteristics protected by law.





Individuals who have a disability and would like to request an accommodation with regard to the application and selection process (i.e. the online application or interviews) or have questions regarding our website accessibility, may call 973-560-6662.







Shift: First Shift
